media:group.media:title: Strandbeest's pumping wings
media:group.media:description:
Wind, wind, wind, wind
If you repeat the word ‘wind’ often enough, it will start blowing. Try it some time. The negligible amount of wind produced by one’s mouth picks up by degrees to become a breeze and in some cases even a full-fledged storm. An atmosphere filled with hundreds of words can’t avoid the meaning of those words. You’ll see. It starts blowing sooner or later.
